{
  "name": "RPlog_Interrogation_-_Face_Off",
  "title": "Interrogating Captain Caiton",
  "summary": "Aboard the NRSD Reprisal, Luke Skywalker, Johanna, and the pilot Rook are summoned by Admiral Rodriga to interrogate a captured Imperial Naval Captain, the doctor Lynae Caiton, kidnapped from her post by the ex-officer Tal'sin. Luke recognizes Caiton through the Force as one of those who tortured his student Brandis Finian. While Luke quietly probes her mind, the volatile Johanna leads a savage verbal assault, even drawing a blade and threatening vivisection, but the coldly composed Caiton parries every taunt, lecturing Johanna on the art of torture and proclaiming her unbending devotion to the Emperor. A furious Admiral Rodriga storms in to demand answers and threatens her life, but Caiton remains utterly unbroken and thoroughly conditioned. Concluding that conventional interrogation is futile, Luke finally invokes a Force mind-trick, commanding Caiton to answer every question with complete honesty before leading Johanna out.",
